groups.label: In order to progress your Fitness for Work Assessment at Redimed Total Health Solutions, the assessing doctor requires further medical information to make a determination regarding your capacity for work.
Please return to your treating practitioner to obtain the following information, where applicable;
Correspondence reports from Specialist outlining surgery performed and progress.
Investigation Reports including x-rays, CTs, Ultrasound, MRI, Echo Stress Test, ECG from the past 12 months.
Pathology results from the past 6 months
Allied Health Correspondences including physiotherapy, chiropractic, occupational therapy, exercise rehab reports

Should this information be received within 3 business days of the scheduled appointment, your finalised report will be provided to your employer. If Redimed does not receive all required information within this time, a report will be provided to your employer which may not determine in full your capacity to return to work.
Please forward all medical reports and results to Redimed via email to medicolegal@redimed.com.au, or fax on (08) 9230 0999.
